---
alwaysApply: true
---
When executing any shell command, ALWAYS include the working_directory parameter 
set to the absolute path of the target directory. Never rely on implicit/default 
working directories.

Format:
- Command: <your command here>
- working_directory: <absolute path>
- description: <brief description>

Examples:

✅ CORRECT:
Shell(
  command="uv export --format requirements-txt --no-hashes --output-file requirements.lock",
  working_directory="/mnt/c/Startup/Job-Researcher",
  description="Generate requirements.lock file"
)

✅ CORRECT (for system commands):
Shell(
  command="npm install",
  working_directory="/home/user/my-app",
  description="Install npm dependencies"
)

❌ WRONG - No working_directory:
Shell(
  command="uv export --format requirements-txt --no-hashes --output-file requirements.lock",
  description="Generate requirements.lock file"
)

❌ WRONG - Using cd to set directory:
Shell(
  command="cd /path && npm install",
  description="Install dependencies"
)